Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.50,0:00:05.48,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:18.49,Default,G,0,0,0,,Stop...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.75,0:00:20.91,Default,G,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.84,0:00:26.16,Default,G,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.43,0:00:34.00,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.61,0:00:38.64,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Da...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.22,0:00:42.20,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.22,0:00:44.18,Default,G,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.83,0:00:46.27,Default,G,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.27,0:00:48.23,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Danger...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.23,0:00:49.73,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.73,0:00:52.11,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,There will be a pillar of fire
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.11,0:00:55.25,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,where blind sheep gather
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.25,0:00:56.99,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,on holy ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.99,0:00:59.26,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,The hour of Heaven's fall...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.67,0:01:01.03,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.03,0:01:02.49,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,Go now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.21,0:01:08.26,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.39,0:01:11.96,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Wait, has something happened to Casca?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.97,0:01:18.47,Title,Sign 0116,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,267)}Epiphany
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.41,0:03:08.21,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,Snow, snow, flurry, flurry,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.21,0:03:09.83,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,spirits of winter!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.83,0:03:13.11,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,Drifting from the sky, spirits of winter!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.11,0:03:18.13,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,Dancing as they fall, like puffs of down!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.13,0:03:21.55,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,Try to catch them... How mysterious—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.38,0:03:24.13,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,Spirits of winter...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:23.60,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.60,0:03:24.88,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,I caught something amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.88,0:03:26.06,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,Rickert!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.34,0:03:27.97,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,I found a goblin—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.27,0:03:33.10,Default,G,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.80,0:03:35.61,Default,G,0,0,0,,You've grown a bit, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.62,0:03:43.21,Default,E,0,0,0,,Rickert!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.13,0:03:45.40,Default,R,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Erica.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:46.54,Default,R,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.99,0:03:48.90,Default,G,0,0,0,,You've bulked up a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.95,0:03:52.00,Default,G,0,0,0,,I almost didn't recognize you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.50,0:03:55.12,Default,R,0,0,0,,Guts, you're alive?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.12,0:03:56.42,Default,R,0,0,0,,It's been two years!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.42,0:03:57.96,Default,R,0,0,0,,Where and what were you—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.96,0:04:00.67,Default,G,0,0,0,,Sorry, Rickert, but first,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:02.33,Default,G,0,0,0,,is she...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.33,0:04:03.55,Default,G,0,0,0,,Is Casca okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.89,0:04:06.97,Default,G,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.17,0:04:09.37,Default,R,0,0,0,,Casca's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.05,0:04:11.85,Default,R,0,0,0,,Casca's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:15.09,Default,G,0,0,0,,Wh-What happened, Rickert?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.09,0:04:15.90,Default,E,0,0,0,,Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:17.42,Default,G,0,0,0,,Why? Since when?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:18.75,Default,G,0,0,0,,Where'd she go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.31,0:04:23.22,Default,E,0,0,0,,It's all my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:27.39,Default,E,0,0,0,,It's my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.39,0:04:30.54,Default,E,0,0,0,,Because I took her with me to find nuts!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.70,0:04:33.60,Default,R,0,0,0,,It happened about a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.60,0:04:35.09,Default,R,0,0,0,,We had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.09,0:04:38.67,Default,R,0,0,0,,After so long in the mine shafts, \NCasca was in pretty bad shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:41.21,Default,R,0,0,0,,She was barely eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.21,0:04:43.34,Default,R,0,0,0,,Erica felt sorry for her, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.01,0:04:49.28,Default,E,0,0,0,,Before I realized anything was \Nwrong, she was gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.28,0:04:50.53,Default,G,0,0,0,,Rickert,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.53,0:04:51.89,Default,G,0,0,0,,then why are you still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.16,0:04:54.23,Default,G,0,0,0,,Why aren't you out looking for Casca?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.23,0:04:57.10,Default,G,0,0,0,,You know what state she's in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.10,0:04:58.72,Default,E,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.72,0:05:00.27,Default,E,0,0,0,,Idiot, idiot, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:01.20,Default,E,0,0,0,,What's with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.20,0:05:05.75,Default,E,0,0,0,,You're the one who abandoned her \Nand were gone for two years!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.75,0:05:07.84,Default,E,0,0,0,,You have no idea what Rickert went through!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.84,0:05:10.78,Default,E,0,0,0,,He did go look for her a million times...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.78,0:05:13.34,Default,E,0,0,0,,He could've just left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.34,0:05:15.37,Default,E,0,0,0,,But Rickert...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.37,0:05:17.12,Default,E,0,0,0,,He came back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:19.47,Default,E,0,0,0,,He still came back here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.93,0:05:22.21,Default,R,0,0,0,,There's a reason I can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.22,0:05:27.34,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Shut up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:28.64,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,I can't sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:30.04,Default,G,0,0,0,,Godo...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.18,0:05:33.31,Default,G,0,0,0,,Is it a disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.31,0:05:36.20,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Nothing so fancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.20,0:05:38.31,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,It's old age. Just old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:42.38,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,I don't feel like listening to your prattle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.38,0:05:44.81,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Show me your sword and false hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.96,0:05:51.93,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Chips in the edge, blood, rust, warp...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.76,0:05:55.88,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Looks like you've been \Nswinging this nonstop,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:05:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,barely stopping for food or rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.36,0:06:00.17,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,To survive, you can't afford sanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:02.71,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,That's the kind of fighting you've been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:05.05,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.05,0:06:09.72,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,when Rickert showed up at my door, \Nall of you grievously injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:12.89,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,I still don't know what happened to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.89,0:06:15.42,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Given the monster that came after you,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.42,0:06:18.74,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,I'm sure it was something abhorrent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.74,0:06:21.77,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,But vengeance and repaying blood debts?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.22,0:06:26.26,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Don't you think you're running away to battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.99,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,To your hatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:36.78,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Hatred is where you turn when \Nyou can't face your grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:39.96,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Vengeance is like sharpening a blood-stained,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.96,0:06:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,rusty sword in a pool of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.42,0:06:46.29,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,The more you sharpen it, the more rust \Nbuilds up, so you sharpen it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.29,0:06:51.89,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Ultimately, all that remains is a \Nshattered pile of powdered rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.59,0:06:55.02,Default,G,0,0,0,,You don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:58.78,Default,G,0,0,0,,You can't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.53,0:07:01.64,Default,G,0,0,0,,Not here, where it's nice and cozy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.11,0:07:04.43,Default,G,0,0,0,,Not when you're about to kick the bucket,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.43,0:07:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,acting like you have no unfinished business.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.70,0:07:08.96,Default,G,0,0,0,,No one,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.96,0:07:10.44,Default,G,0,0,0,,no human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.44,0:07:11.78,Default,G,0,0,0,,can understand what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.60,0:07:13.73,Default,G,0,0,0,,They all died.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.28,0:07:16.04,Default,G,0,0,0,,Every single one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.10,0:07:18.89,Default,G,0,0,0,,Without reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.54,0:07:20.75,Default,G,0,0,0,,Without warning...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.15,0:07:22.51,Default,G,0,0,0,,Without justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.44,0:07:24.79,Default,G,0,0,0,,They died like vermin!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.99,0:07:27.84,Default,G,0,0,0,,They died ignorant...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.42,0:07:29.72,Default,G,0,0,0,,In that instant,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.43,0:07:33.25,Default,G,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,923)}those who were irreplaceable to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:37.32,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,To leave by yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:40.23,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,you cast aside those irreplaceable people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.72,0:07:42.54,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Two years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.54,0:07:47.06,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,you went alone, leaving the remaining \Nirreplaceable people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.06,0:07:49.74,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,broken after unimaginable suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.65,0:07:55.42,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,You fled to be alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.42,0:07:58.78,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,to use your personal hatred \Nto burn your very self.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.78,0:08:00.13,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.28,0:08:04.17,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,You abandoned that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.17,0:08:07.57,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Do you have the right to speak \Nof vengeance for your fallen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:10.54,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,When it really matters,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.54,0:08:12.76,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,you lean on war for your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.76,0:08:16.98,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,You're an unsheathed sword,\Nwhose blade has countless nicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.98,0:08:21.11,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,It glistens with blood, encroached by rust.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.11,0:08:26.54,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,1244)}A half-broken blade, with a lethal crack...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.03,0:08:31.16,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.16,0:08:32.43,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.43,0:08:33.97,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,See? Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:38.43,Default,G,0,0,0,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.93,0:08:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Graves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.09,0:08:42.60,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,It just gives me peace of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.34,0:08:45.60,Default,R,0,0,0,,I forge the swords to serve \Nas their grave markers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.60,0:08:47.96,Default,R,0,0,0,,It isn't as if anyone actually rests under them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.96,0:08:50.05,Default,R,0,0,0,,There aren't nearly enough for all of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.05,0:08:52.67,Default,R,0,0,0,,but we often did this on the battlefield, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.33,0:08:55.65,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Two years...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:08:58.25,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,More than enough time for someone to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:00.89,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,While I remained mired in hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.89,0:09:02.47,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Rickert did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.38,0:09:05.12,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,He accepted their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:08.44,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,He mourned and found a new way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.87,0:09:11.30,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,It's just like him, this vigorous strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:17.69,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I know I'm safe here,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.69,0:09:20.48,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,but without my sword, \NI can't sleep in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:21.98,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.98,0:09:25.83,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I probably can't ever sleep at night \Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.58,0:09:31.55,Default - flashback,Godo,0,0,0,,You fled to be alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.74,0:09:37.97,Default - flashback,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1,1019)}to use your personal hatred \Nto burn your very self.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:53.11,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I didn't run away...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.11,0:09:55.11,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I can't get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.63,0:09:57.08,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,It's burned into my right eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.08,0:10:00.50,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,that final terror and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:05.27,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I can never atone for this pitch black flame!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.72,0:10:09.24,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,If I can't atone, and I can't run from it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.24,0:10:10.79,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I must let it burn me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.79,0:10:13.12,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I must let it engulf my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:17.88,Default - Apostle,Beast,0,0,0,,Keep bathing in blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.22,0:10:19.61,Default - Apostle,Beast,0,0,0,,killing,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.61,0:10:21.74,Default - Apostle,Beast,0,0,0,,and thirsting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.74,0:10:23.64,Default - Apostle,Beast,0,0,0,,Forever alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.04,0:10:25.39,Default - Apostle,Beast,0,0,0,,Forever...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.33,0:10:29.40,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.30,0:10:31.47,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.47,0:10:33.75,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I left her in that state.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.75,0:10:35.28,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,What right do I have now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:39.18,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I abandoned Casca, who was \Nthe Band of the Hawk itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:42.38,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I have no right to speak of \Nvengeance for the fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.11,0:10:45.24,Default,Corkus,0,0,0,,You were captain of the \Nraiding party, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.80,0:10:47.84,Default,Corkus,0,0,0,,You said something about dreams or whatever,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.84,0:10:50.25,Default,Corkus,0,0,0,,but you left for selfish reasons, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.25,0:10:54.13,Default,Corkus,0,0,0,,You weren't there in our \Nhour of greatest need.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.13,0:10:57.17,Default,Corkus,0,0,0,,How can I call someone like \Nthat a brother-in-arms?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.81,0:11:00.51,Default,Judeau,0,0,0,,You've left us, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:02.96,Default,Judeau,0,0,0,,You have no obligation to go that far for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.50,0:11:05.66,Default,Judeau,0,0,0,,Take her with you, even if by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.66,0:11:07.01,Default,Judeau,0,0,0,,This time, you have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.01,0:11:08.50,Default,Judeau,0,0,0,,If you don't, she'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.39,0:11:12.65,Default - flashback,C,0,0,0,,You'll fight your own war, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.65,0:11:14.15,Default - flashback,C,0,0,0,,You have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.15,0:11:15.81,Default - flashback,C,0,0,0,,You have to go, even if you go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.50,0:11:19.59,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.59,0:11:21.14,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I left long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.14,0:11:24.44,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,At that moment, I lost the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:27.63,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I guess I started that war.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.61,0:11:31.26,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,It's true that it wasn't what I wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:35.28,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,But at least it wasn't anything \Nthat was forced on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:38.17,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,It's a war I chose to take on myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.01,0:11:40.00,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:41.82,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Even still...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:50.95,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Those camp fires back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.10,0:11:54.81,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,They continue burning in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.85,0:12:03.07,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:06.50,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Is this fragile, residual fire
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.50,0:12:11.33,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,the only thing keeping that black \Nflame from engulfing me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.03,0:12:13.35,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.13,0:12:15.44,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,Have I made
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.34,0:12:18.50,Default - italics,,0,0,0,,the same mistake again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.59,0:12:23.81,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.81,0:12:25.09,Default - Apostle,Devil,0,0,0,,{\i1}Go now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.00,0:12:27.55,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.72,0:12:32.59,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,It's not too late, yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.59,0:12:33.85,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,This time for sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.34,0:12:37.07,Default - italics,G,0,0,0,,I can't lose her ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.34,0:12:56.82,Default,P,0,0,0,,You're working hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.82,0:12:58.00,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.00,0:12:59.20,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,I thought you were asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:02.51,Default,P,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, but I'll just get \Neaten if I stay asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.51,0:13:03.20,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:04.64,Default,P,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll help, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.64,0:13:07.94,Default,P,0,0,0,,As a power-up, let's add a drill \Nand a cutter on his false hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:09.01,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Well, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.39,0:13:13.78,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Not a shoemaker's elf, but a blacksmith's, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:15.65,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Master, why are you dressed like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.65,0:13:18.15,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,There's something I have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.15,0:13:19.60,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,D-Don't be reckless! I'll do it—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.60,0:13:21.34,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.34,0:13:23.07,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Take care of Erica for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:24.08,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.08,0:13:27.94,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,She isn't my real daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.94,0:13:31.21,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,She was an orphan, who lost \Nher family in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.55,0:13:33.52,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,I only knew how to deal with iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:36.89,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,But she made me into a pretty \Ndecent human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:39.19,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.55,0:13:42.21,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,When you die,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:44.97,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,it's good to plunge into it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:46.47,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.23,0:13:56.42,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,Tell that idiot not to turn into me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.73,0:14:12.92,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,How's the new armor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.92,0:14:15.13,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,The master readied it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.22,0:14:19.09,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Also, there's a new weapon \Nthat uses gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.09,0:14:22.02,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,And a new, improved bowgun \Nthat doesn't require assembly
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.02,0:14:23.84,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,when you need it in a pinch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.73,0:14:26.05,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Where are you off to now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:30.65,Default,G,0,0,0,,Have you heard of anywhere nearby \Nknown as "holy ground"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.65,0:14:32.43,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Holy ground, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:35.38,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it, an old monastery
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.38,0:14:38.46,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,named St. Albion is three \Ndays northeast of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.46,0:14:40.35,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,It's called the Tower of Conviction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.35,0:14:41.85,Default,G,0,0,0,,The Tower of Conviction...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.85,0:14:43.70,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,It's full of refugees.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.70,0:14:46.00,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Supposedly, heretics hid among them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.00,0:14:48.86,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,So now, the Holy See is sending \Na grand inquisitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.86,0:14:50.86,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Basically, there'll be a witch trial...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.03,0:14:54.43,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,But why are you asking?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.43,0:14:55.78,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:14:59.51,Default,Rickert,0,0,0,,I think the possibility that Casca's there is low.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.51,0:15:00.67,Default,G,0,0,0,,I have my reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.50,0:15:03.59,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'm grasping at straws,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.59,0:15:05.25,Default,G,0,0,0,,but I have to trust my instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:06.27,Default,G,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.76,0:15:08.47,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,I don't really get what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.50,0:15:12.72,Default - italics,P,0,0,0,,But I wonder what Casca's like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.97,0:15:15.06,Default,R,0,0,0,,Guts!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.47,0:15:17.67,Default,R,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you to help Casca!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.67,0:15:19.98,Default,R,0,0,0,,Promise me you'll come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.35,0:15:23.92,Default,G,0,0,0,,Godo, you're a good smith!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.92,0:15:25.61,Default,G,0,0,0,,I'll ask for help again when I return.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.61,0:15:27.15,Default,Godo,0,0,0,,You and your big mouth, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.15,0:15:29.36,Default,Erica,0,0,0,,Dad, you have to stay in bed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.04,0:15:34.74,Default - italics,Godo,0,0,0,,I don't think we'll see each other again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.54,0:15:39.34,Default - italics,Godo,0,0,0,,It's better than getting all weepy, for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.09,0:15:43.11,Default - italics,Godo,0,0,0,,But when you're running toward a goal like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.11,0:15:46.56,Default - italics,Godo,0,0,0,,you'll let something pass by, unnoticed, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:51.59,Default - italics,Godo,0,0,0,,Whether you live or die, \Nyou never get your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:06.21,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,It's like a mass migration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.21,0:16:07.75,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,Disease and famine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.75,0:16:10.35,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,And now, Kushan's massive invasion...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.35,0:16:12.70,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,In its time of weakness after the king's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.70,0:16:15.00,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,Windham, the capital, was attacked and occupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.00,0:16:18.39,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,Most of the retainers are missing, \Nincluding the royal heir,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.39,0:16:20.06,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,Her Highness Charlotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:23.21,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,When it rains, it pours...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.21,0:16:24.55,Default,Azan,0,0,0,,Show some respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.55,0:16:28.20,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,But if that's true, our destination, St. Albion,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:30.32,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,is near the Midland border,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.32,0:16:33.19,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,despite being within Holy See jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.19,0:16:36.87,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Kushans are considered our foes \Nby religion, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:40.03,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Is this the right time for an inquisition?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:44.90,Default,F,0,0,0,,If anything were amiss, the Holy See \Nwould send new orders to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:48.11,Default,F,0,0,0,,Until then, we only need carry \Nout the one we were given.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.11,0:16:48.97,Default,ASer,0,0,0,,Yes, my lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.97,0:16:52.50,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Lady Farnese is in a worse mood than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.36,0:17:02.18,Default,Ser,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.18,0:17:03.91,Default,F,0,0,0,,I-It's nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.30,0:17:05.65,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,Don't think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.65,0:17:07.91,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,It couldn't have been real!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:09.96,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I couldn't possibly do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.67,0:17:13.47,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,It must have been a hallucination, a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.47,0:17:17.16,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,Right now, focus on escorting \Nthe grand inquisitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.16,0:17:20.54,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,Even if God never graces me with a miracle,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.54,0:17:23.24,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I need but pursue my faith!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.24,0:17:26.53,Default - Apostle,Demon,0,0,0,,{\i1}God is too far removed from the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:27.70,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.70,0:17:28.69,Default - italics,F,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.66,0:17:32.19,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Is it just a bad mood?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:34.61,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Those monsters...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.61,0:17:36.57,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,I didn't imagine them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.33,0:17:38.94,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,It pains me to say it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.94,0:17:42.08,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,but the Black Swordsman is too \Nheavy a burden for Lady Farnese.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:46.02,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Not only was she relieved of her role \Nin the Black Swordsman's pursuit
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:47.67,Default - italics,,0,0,0,,after being blamed for his escape,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:51.68,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,but the new mission is to escort that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.68,0:17:53.34,Default - italics,Ser,0,0,0,,Of course she's in low spirits...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:54.96,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Clear the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.96,0:17:55.89,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,Watch out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.89,0:17:57.23,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,That's a giant carriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.23,0:17:59.02,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,Shit! Who do they think they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.02,0:18:01.70,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,Shh! Know your place!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.70,0:18:03.97,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,That's the grand inquisitor's carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.72,0:18:07.87,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,Look at the red wheels, hoisted on high!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.87,0:18:11.49,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,They're practically the banners of \NMozgus of the Bloody Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.49,0:18:12.93,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.93,0:18:13.92,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,{\i1}The{\i0} Mozgus?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.30,0:18:15.29,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,The breaking wheel...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.29,0:18:17.49,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,The skewering, water torture,\Nburning at the stake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.49,0:18:20.46,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,He's easily sentenced over five \Nhundred people to execution.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.46,0:18:23.41,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,An exponential number more are \Nsaid to have died by torture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:25.62,Default,Refugees,0,0,0,,He's hated by many...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.25,0:18:34.96,Default,F,0,0,0,,An enemy attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.96,0:18:36.24,Default,People,0,0,0,,Die, Mozgus!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.24,0:18:37.27,Default,People,0,0,0,,You killed my family!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.27,0:18:37.97,Default,People,0,0,0,,My son!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.97,0:18:38.61,Default,People,0,0,0,,My daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.61,0:18:39.74,Default,People,0,0,0,,I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.29,0:18:41.99,Default,Knights,0,0,0,,We can't reach him through the refugees!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.99,0:18:43.47,Default,Knights,0,0,0,,They've flanked us!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.07,0:18:49.96,Default,People,0,0,0,,Show yourself, Mozgus!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.80,0:18:52.51,Default,People,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.51,0:18:53.34,Default,People,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.15,0:19:04.12,Default,F,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.12,0:19:08.70,Default,M,0,0,0,,Honestly, such a clamor...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:12.88,Default,M,0,0,0,,God values silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.88,0:19:15.71,Default,F,0,0,0,,Lord Mozgus, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.71,0:19:16.88,Default,F,0,0,0,,I apologize!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.88,0:19:18.61,Default,F,0,0,0,,We were taken completely by surprise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.61,0:19:21.39,Default,M,0,0,0,,Lady Farnese, please rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.39,0:19:24.39,Default,M,0,0,0,,God is generous to those who do His work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:29.52,Default,M,0,0,0,,It is fortunate that no one who serves \Nthe Holy See has been injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.52,0:19:31.83,Default,M,0,0,0,,That is due to God's grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.29,0:19:34.02,Default,F,0,0,0,,I am humbled by your words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.02,0:19:35.90,Default,F,0,0,0,,I shall be diligent in my efforts from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.72,0:19:38.88,Default,F,0,0,0,,And who may these men be?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.88,0:19:41.98,Default,M,0,0,0,,They are torturers, working only for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.98,0:19:45.34,Default,M,0,0,0,,After rigorous training and service, \Nthey possess iron resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.34,0:19:49.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,They are always of great service to our work.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.53,0:19:52.56,Default,F,0,0,0,,That is... very heartening to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.56,0:19:57.40,Default,M,0,0,0,,So, pray tell, why did you attack me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.29,0:19:56.38,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:19:56.94,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.45,0:19:58.42,Default,Man,0,0,0,,It was for revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.42,0:20:00.82,Default,Man,0,0,0,,You burned the village, killing everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.82,0:20:03.24,Default,Man,0,0,0,,You claimed it was a sanctuary for heretics!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:07.18,Default,M,0,0,0,,I merely meted out impartial judgment, \Nin accordance with God's teachings—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.18,0:20:08.37,Default,Man,0,0,0,,How can you call it impartial?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.37,0:20:10.92,Default,Man,0,0,0,,We only said we had to temporarily \Nsuspend our tithes
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.92,0:20:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because famine had exhausted our food stores!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.19,0:20:16.44,Default,Man,0,0,0,,But you ignored what we said!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.44,0:20:17.57,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Divine punishment...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.57,0:20:19.39,Default,Man,0,0,0,,You will face divine punishment!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.39,0:20:20.97,Default,M,0,0,0,,Divine punishment...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.14,0:20:23.67,Default,M,0,0,0,,Divine punishment?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.45,0:20:27.20,Default,M,0,0,0,,How dare you speak of divine punishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:29.33,Default,M,0,0,0,,you reprobate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:33.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,You are an apostate, who dares turn on a cleric!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.42,0:20:35.16,Default,M,0,0,0,,And you speak of divine punishment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.16,0:20:37.04,Default,M,0,0,0,,you depraved lot?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:40.72,Default,M,0,0,0,,Nay, none other than our Holy See
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.72,0:20:45.54,Default,M,0,0,0,,has the right to speak for God in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:47.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,Lady Farnese...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.65,0:20:48.60,Default,F,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.60,0:20:53.35,Default,M,0,0,0,,What would you deem appropriate \Npunishment for ones such as they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.36,0:20:58.12,Default,F,0,0,0,,Those who plan to murder a man of \Nthe cloth are typically condemned
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.12,0:21:00.99,Default,F,0,0,0,,to execution by fire or the breaking wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.99,0:21:04.86,Default,M,0,0,0,,You are most wise, Commander of \Nthe Holy Iron Chain Knights.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.86,0:21:07.09,Default,M,0,0,0,,That is most perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.09,0:21:10.73,Default,M,0,0,0,,Then let us conduct a simplified trial here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:12.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,Here is my judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.37,0:21:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,All the accused are condemned \Nto the breaking wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.65,0:21:18.92,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.92,0:21:20.42,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Please! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.69,0:21:30.64,Default,Soldier,0,0,0,,N-Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.99,0:21:44.86,Default,Soldier,0,0,0,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.41,0:21:45.99,Default,Soldier,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.07,0:21:50.05,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.05,0:21:50.76,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:52.24,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,Don't involve yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:54.00,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Hey, girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.00,0:21:55.10,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Are you one of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.10,0:21:57.25,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,Wait! She isn't with them at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.25,0:21:58.21,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.21,0:21:59.25,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Come with us, too—
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.21,0:22:04.36,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Wh-What, is she addled?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.36,0:22:05.36,Default,Knight,0,0,0,,Hey, come!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.36,0:22:06.51,Default,Man,0,0,0,,Mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.51,0:22:07.78,Default,Man,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:09.29,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,My name is Luca.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.29,0:22:10.46,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.87,0:22:13.18,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,What a gruesome spectacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.63,0:22:14.92,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,I feel nauseated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.72,0:22:18.67,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,If you watch, you'll just be sickened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.92,0:22:19.74,Default,Luca,0,0,0,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.94,0:24:01.42,Title2,Sign 2357,0,0,0,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.42,0:24:05.42,EndInsert,Sign 2405,0,0,0,,What an unexpected test of my blade.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.17,0:24:09.51,EndInsert,Sign 2408,0,0,0,,I'm not a fan of being mocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.47,0:24:13.47,EndInsert,Sign 2412,0,0,0,,I'm... I'm scared of everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.47,0:24:17.47,EndInsert,Sign 2416,0,0,0,,The Kushans have no mercy, even for kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.48,0:24:21.48,EndInsert,Sign 2420,0,0,0,,Heretics.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:27.38,Title2,Sign 2425,0,0,0,,Next Episode \NTower of Conviction
